Subject: Re: [T2] Best SVDA dizzy.

On Wednesday, March 17, 2010, at 06:54AM, "John Kolak" <jkolak(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:

>I am using the Hot Spark SVDA. Works well except at max advance the
>timing mark is not steady. Anyone familiar with this symptom and
>whether or not it is acceptable? Or how to fix?

If it's identical to the Pertronix, some of the magnets in the sleeve that fits over the distributor shaft may not be exactly 90 deg. from the others. This causes the timing to move by a degree or so under timing light inspection.

If there is wild fluctuation at max advance, maybe it's the hot spark causing the problem or perhaps the spark event is erratic due to combustion problems?

Regarding the subject:

